  "prompt": "What is a short circuit, and what is short circuiting (in simple English)?",
  "response": "A short circuit is a situation in an electrical system where electricity takes an unintended path, usually with little or no resistance. This often happens when two conductors, such as wires, come into contact with each other because of a fault, like damaged insulation. Instead of flowing through the intended circuit, the electricity flows directly between the conductors, which can cause overheating, a breakdown in the circuit, or even a fire.\n\nShort-circuiting, in a broader context, refers to situations where a process is bypassed, often in an unintended or abrupt way, to take a quicker route that skips important steps. In both cases\u2014electrical short circuits and process short-circuiting\u2014the \"short cut\" usually leads to problems or failures.",
